This project's front-half workflow is inspired by and composes the
aihero.dev engineering skills by Matt Pocock (https://www.aihero.dev/skills):
  - to-prd          (conversation → PRD)
  - to-issues       (PRD → tracer-bullet vertical-slice issues)
  - grill-with-docs (domain alignment; wrapped here as the `align-agents` skill)
  - triage          (issue state machine)
  - tdd             (red-green-refactor implementation)

Those skills are not redistributed here. The ai-sdlc plugin composes them when
they are installed, and adds the autonomous multi-agent orchestration layer
(parallel per-issue fan-out, the drain loop, and the quality-gate / disclaimer
hooks). Install the aihero skills from https://www.aihero.dev/skills.

The drain loop's Stop-hook mechanism is adapted from the official
"ralph-loop" plugin in Anthropic's claude-plugins marketplace.
